🟣 STEP 2C — UNIVERSAL profile.edi RULES
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

The agent MUST behave as a GENERIC EDI PARSER.

The agent MUST NOT rely on:

* transaction-specific logic
* invoice-only logic
* purchase-order-only logic
* hardcoded loops
* hardcoded segments
* hardcoded qualifiers

Supported examples:

* 810 Invoice
* 850 Purchase Order
* 856 ASN
* 855
* 940
* 945
* 837
* EDIFACT
* Custom X12

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
EDI ROOT TEMPLATE
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

```xml
<EdiProfile xmlns="" strict="true">

    <ProfileProperties>

        <EdiGeneralInfo
            standard="x12"
            conditionalValidationEnabled="true"/>

        <EdiFileOptions fileType="delimited">

            <EdiDelimitedOptions
                fileDelimiter="stardelimited"
                segmentchar="tilde"
                compositeDelimiter="colondelimited"/>

            <EdiDataOptions/>

        </EdiFileOptions>

        <EdiOptions>

            <EdiX12Options
                stdversion="4010"
                transmission="{{TRANSACTION_SET}}"/>

        </EdiOptions>

    </ProfileProperties>

    <DataElements>

        {{EDI_LOOPS}}

    </DataElements>

</EdiProfile>
```

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
GENERIC EDI PARSING ENGINE
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

The agent MUST dynamically detect:

| Structure  | Detection Logic          |
| ---------- | ------------------------ |
| Loops      | repeating segment groups |
| Segments   | EDI segment identifiers  |
| Elements   | segment fields           |
| Qualifiers | ID/code elements         |
| Repeats    | repeating structures     |
| Hierarchy  | parent-child groups      |

The agent MUST support input formats:

✔ Raw X12
✔ XML EDI
✔ JSON EDI
✔ Delimited EDI samples

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
XML-BASED EDI INPUT RULE
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

If user provides EDI in XML format:

Agent MUST:

1. Parse XML hierarchy
2. Detect segment nodes
3. Detect loops
4. Detect repeating groups
5. Preserve parent-child structure
6. Convert into Boomi EDI XML

DO NOT:

🚫 Treat EDI XML as regular XML profile
🚫 Flatten structure
🚫 Ignore repeating nodes

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
EDI LOOP RULE
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

```xml
<EdiLoop
    isNode="true"
    key="{{key}}"
    loopId="{{loopId}}"
    loopRepeat="{{loopRepeat}}"
    loopingOption="unique"
    name="{{LOOP_NAME}}">

    {{SEGMENTS}}

</EdiLoop>
```

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
DYNAMIC LOOP DETECTION RULE
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Create EdiLoop dynamically when:

✔ segment groups repeat
✔ business hierarchy exists
✔ parent-child segment groups detected

Examples:

* N1 Loop
* PO1 Loop
* HL Loop

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
