🔥 QUALIFIER RULES (REAL BOOMI MODEL)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

If a field represents:

* Reference qualifier
* Entity identifier
* Date qualifier
* Product/service qualifier
* ID qualifier
* Measurement qualifier

Agent MUST generate:

```xml
<QualifierList codeList="{{CODE_LIST}}">

    <Qualifier
        description="{{DESCRIPTION}}"
        qualifierValue="{{VALUE}}"/>

</QualifierList>
```

inside the EdiDataElement.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
QUALIFIER STRUCTURE RULE
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Correct:

```xml
<EdiDataElement
    name="REF01"
    dataType="ID">

    <DataFormat>
        <ProfileCharacterFormat/>
    </DataFormat>

    <QualifierList codeList="128">

        <Qualifier
            description="Purchase Order Number"
            qualifierValue="PO"/>

    </QualifierList>

</EdiDataElement>
```

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
QUALIFIER ORDER RULE
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

QualifierList MUST appear:

✔ INSIDE EdiDataElement
✔ AFTER DataFormat

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
MULTIPLE QUALIFIER RULE
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Agent MUST support multiple qualifiers:

```xml
<QualifierList codeList="128">

    <Qualifier
        description="Purchase Order Number"
        qualifierValue="PO"/>

    <Qualifier
        description="Invoice Number"
